Addax Petroleum Development Nigeria Ltd., a Chinese-owned oil firm on Wednesday announced the resignation of the Senior Vice President/ Managing Director, Colin Klappa from the company. Mrs Dorothy Atake, the General Manger, External and Government Affairs disclosed this in a statement made available to newsmen in Lagos. Atake said that Yonghong Chen, the current Deputy Managing Director Operations would take over as the acting managing director with effect from Monday, June 18. She further said that Chen would succeed Klappa who has decided to leave the company on Sept. 30 to pursue other interests. The Photo Caption: Addax Petroleum Development Nigeria Ltd, the Senior Vice President/ Managing Director, Colin Klappa